snippet.textDisplay:
You guys need to seriously stop picking the low-hanging fruit. The vast majority of your videos are great - hysterically funny, well scripted, well conceived - but come on, picking on superhero, horror and animated films and TV shows is shooting giant fish in a tiny barrel. I know you've done a few of the better flicks like Citizen Kane, Pulp Fiction, Alien, and such, but fuck, give us sins for The Godfather, 12 Angry Men, Casablanca, Doctor Zhivago, Holy Grail, Raging Bull, All About Eve, etc.

I imagine you choose these straw men and easy-to-kill rabbits since they're hugely popular with the American people, but the majority of the American people are imbeciles of the highest order and couldn't comprehend a non-derivative story, and one that cannot go five seconds without manufactured tension, four seconds without CGI, three seconds without a cut, two seconds without score, and one second without mock-up facial lighting. Fuck these morons!

Give us Roman Holiday, for which Audrey Hepburn won an academy award, and in which she was awesome, except for when she cried like a distraught high school teenager on her first broken heart. Blech! Or lambaste the horrible chemistry of Hepburn and Bogart in Sabrina. Or tell us about Singin' in the Rain, in which Donald O'Connor was a superior dancer to Gene Kelly and how Debbie Reynolds wasn't half the actor (I refuse to accept that "actor" is gender-specific, that's racist!) Carrie Fischer was in Star Wars 3 and 4. Or talk about the many, many ways Gone with the Wind would have us believe those darkies were better off with slavery. You know what trouble I's talkin' 'bout... ALL KINDS of ist!

Please raise the bar!
